      "writtenOn": "2026-05-08T21:24:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why not wait to do the clib_memset() until after all checks have passed? You could avoid the memset operation when runtime data cannot be generated for any reason. Presumably a caller can pay attention to the return code and assume that the memory it passed in to hold the runtime data has undefined contents if an error was returned.",
      "revId": "4edf76e4bdf9597a038edea3c04d117978b3af53",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
